</strong></span><span style=\"color: #006699;\"><strong>-></strong></span>a;</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\">    }</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\">}</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\"><span style=\"color: #0053ff;\"><strong>$mon_instance</strong></span> <span style=\"color: #006699;\"><strong>=</strong></span> <span style=\"color: #006699;\"><strong>new</strong></span> <span style=\"color: #a535ae;\">MaClasse</span>(<span style=\"color: #666666;\">\"hello\"</span>);</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\"><span style=\"color: #0053ff;\"><strong>$mon_instance</strong></span><span style=\"color: #006699;\"><strong>-></strong></span>afficher(); <span style=\"color: #af82d4;\">// affiche hello</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\">?-->\r\n</pre>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3 class=\"western\"><a name=\"le-destructeur\"></a><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Le destructeur</span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">La destruction d&rsquo;une instance provoque syst&eacute;matiquement l&rsquo;appel du </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">destructeur</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> de la classe (la m&eacute;thode d&rsquo;instance </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">__destruct</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">). Le r&ocirc;le avou&eacute; du destructeur est de pouvoir d&eacute;truire proprement l&rsquo;objet, par exemple en fermant les ressources utilis&eacute;es par l&rsquo;instance (comme un fichier ouvert avec fopen par exemple). Comme pour le constructeur, cette m&eacute;thode n&rsquo;est pas obligatoire. Dans la r&eacute;alit&eacute;, les usages du destructeur sont assez rares.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Exemple d&rsquo;utilisation du destructeur:</span></p>\r\n<table width=\"618\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\"><colgroup><col width=\"20\" /> <col width=\"590\" /> </colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 0cm;\" width=\"20\">\r\n<pre class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">1</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">2</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">3</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">4</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">5</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">6</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">7</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">8</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">9</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">10</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">11</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">12</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">13</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">14</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">15</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">16</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">17</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">18</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">19</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">20</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">21</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">22</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">23</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">24</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">25</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">26</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">27</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">28</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">29</span></pre>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 0cm;\" width=\"590\">\r\n<pre class=\"western\">&nbsp;</pre>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3 class=\"western\"><a name=\"membres-de-classes-et-membres-dinstances\"></a> <span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Membres de classes et membres d&rsquo;instances</span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Un membre peut &ecirc;tre li&eacute; &agrave; l&rsquo;instance de la classe (on parle alors de </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">membre d&rsquo;instance</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">), c&rsquo;est le cas dans tous les exemples ci-dessus avec </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">$this-&gt;nomDeLaPropriete</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">. Un membre d&rsquo;instance ne peut pas &ecirc;tre utilis&eacute; sans l&rsquo;objet (l&rsquo;instance) qui va avec.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Mais un membre peut &eacute;galement &ecirc;tre directement li&eacute; &agrave; la classe elle-m&ecirc;me plut&ocirc;t qu&rsquo;a ses instances; on parle alors de </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">membre de classe</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> ou de </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>membre statique</strong></span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">. Il est pour cela pr&eacute;c&eacute;d&eacute; du mot cl&eacute; </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">static</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> et on y acc&egrave;de &agrave; l&rsquo;aide de l&rsquo;op&eacute;rateur de r&eacute;solution de port&eacute;e &laquo;&nbsp;</span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">::&nbsp;&raquo;&nbsp;</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">. Au sein d&rsquo;une classe le mot cl&eacute; </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>self</strong></span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> permet d&rsquo;acc&eacute;der aux membres statiques, </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>self</strong></span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> repr&eacute;sente la classe en cours de la m&ecirc;me fa&ccedil;on que </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">$this</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> repr&eacute;sente l&rsquo;instance en cours (le mot cl&eacute; </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">$this</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> n&rsquo;est pas disponible au sein d&rsquo;un membre statique et son utilisation provoquera une erreur fatale).</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">La visibilit&eacute; s&rsquo;applique de la m&ecirc;me fa&ccedil;on sur les membres d&rsquo;instances et sur les membres de classes, leurs effets sont basiquement les m&ecirc;mes sauf dans le cas de l&rsquo;h&eacute;ritage de m&eacute;thodes statiques que nous d&eacute;taillerons plus bas.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Exemple de classe disposant de membres statiques:</span></p>\r\n<table width=\"458\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\"><colgroup><col width=\"20\" /> <col width=\"430\" /> </colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 0cm;\" width=\"20\">\r\n<pre class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">1</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">2</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">3</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">4</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">5</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">6</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">7</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">8</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">9</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">10</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">11</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">12</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">13</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">14</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">15</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">16</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">17</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">18</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">19</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">20</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">21</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">22</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">23</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">24</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">25</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">26</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">27</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">28</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">29</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">30</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">31</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">32</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">33</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">34</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">35</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">36</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">37</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">38</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">39</span></pre>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 0cm;\" width=\"430\">\r\n<pre class=\"western\">&nbsp;</pre>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h2 class=\"western\"><a name=\"lh&eacute;ritage\"></a><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">L&rsquo;h&eacute;ritage</span></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Avec l&rsquo;h&eacute;ritage, on entre dans la vraie plus-value des langages objets par rapport aux langages imp&eacute;ratifs, il s&rsquo;agit d&rsquo;un moyen simple de favoriser la </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>r&eacute;utilisabilit&eacute;</strong></span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> du code.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">L&rsquo;h&eacute;ritage va permettre une r&eacute;utilisation verticale du code, c&rsquo;est &agrave; dire que nos classes vont former une hi&eacute;rarchie dans laquelle les enfants (les </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">classes filles</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">) pourront r&eacute;utiliser les comportements et les donn&eacute;es de leur(s) parent(s) (les </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">classes m&egrave;res</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">).</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">TR&Egrave;S </span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Important</span></strong><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">: l&rsquo;h&eacute;ritage entre deux classes caract&eacute;rise la relation </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">&ldquo;</span></em><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>est un esp&egrave;ce de&hellip;</strong></span></em><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">&ldquo;</span></em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Par exemple: une voiture est une esp&egrave;ce de v&eacute;hicule, un chien est une esp&egrave;ce d&rsquo;animal. L&rsquo;h&eacute;ritage doit &ecirc;tre s&eacute;mantiquement valide afin d&rsquo;&eacute;viter les d&eacute;rives comme l&rsquo;h&eacute;ritage fonctionnel. Comme le disait mon prof de Java: </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">&ldquo;</span></em><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>ce n&rsquo;est pas parce que le chien pisse sur le poteau que le chien est un esp&egrave;ce de poteau</strong></span></em><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">&rdquo;</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">&hellip; Donc ce n&rsquo;est pas parce que le chien </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">utilise</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> le poteau qu&rsquo;il doit </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">h&eacute;riter</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> de poteau.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Concr&egrave;tement</span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">, lorsqu&rsquo;une classe B (la </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">fille</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">) h&eacute;rite d&rsquo;une classe A (la </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">m&egrave;re</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">), elle dispose alors de tous les membres publics </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">et prot&eacute;g&eacute;s</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> de sa m&egrave;re (</span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>d&rsquo;o&ugrave;</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong> l&rsquo;importance de cette diff&eacute;rentiation entre membre prot&eacute;g&eacute; et priv&eacute;</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">). On r&eacute;alise un h&eacute;ritage quand il y a lieu d&rsquo;effectuer une </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">sp&eacute;cialisation</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">, c&rsquo;est &agrave; dire que la classe fille va </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">red&eacute;finir</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> (on parle aussi de </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">surcharge</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">) ou </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">ajouter</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> des comportements.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Pour que la classe B h&eacute;rite de A, on utilise le mot cl&eacute; </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>extends</strong></span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> comme montr&eacute; ci-dessous. On peut, depuis une classe fille, faire explicitement appel au m&eacute;thode de la classe parente &agrave; l&rsquo;aide du mot cl&eacute; </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>parent</strong></span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">, c&rsquo;est pratique lorsqu&rsquo;il s&rsquo;agit de r&eacute;utiliser une partie du comportement de la classe parent sans pour autant devoir le r&eacute;&eacute;crire.</span></p>\r\n<table width=\"722\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\"><colgroup><col width=\"20\" /> <col width=\"694\" /> </colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 0cm;\" width=\"20\">\r\n<pre class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">1</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">2</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">3</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">4</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">5</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">6</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">7</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">8</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">9</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">10</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">11</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">12</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">13</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">14</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">15</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">16</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">17</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">18</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">19</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">20</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">21</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">22</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">23</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">24</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">25</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">26</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">27</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">28</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">29</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">30</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">31</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">32</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">33</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">34</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">35</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">36</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">37</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">38</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">39</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">40</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">41</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">42</span></pre>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 0cm;\" width=\"694\">\r\n<pre class=\"western\">&nbsp;</pre>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Important</span></strong><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">: En PHP, l&rsquo;h&eacute;ritage multiple </span><strong><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">n&rsquo;existe pas</span></strong><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">. Ce qui signifie que vous ne pouvez par d&eacute;clarer une classe qui h&eacute;rite de deux autres classes. En somme, </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">class\r\nA extends B, C</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> c&rsquo;est interdit. Vous pouvez en revanche </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">r&eacute;aliser</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> plusieurs interfaces (voir le chapitre sur le polymorphisme ci-dessous).</span></p>\r\n<h3 class=\"western\"><a name=\"filliation-parents-enfants-et-arbre-g&eacute;n&eacute;alogique\"></a> <span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Filliation, parents, enfants et arbre g&eacute;n&eacute;alogique</span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Une classe n&rsquo;est pas seulement un moyen commode de rassembler des donn&eacute;es et des comportements au sein d&rsquo;une structure, c&rsquo;est surtout un excellent moyen de cr&eacute;er de nouveaux </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">types</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> de donn&eacute;es, car en r&eacute;alit&eacute; une classe peut &ecirc;tre consid&eacute;r&eacute;e comme un type au m&ecirc;me sens qu&rsquo;une </span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">cha&icirc;ne</span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> ou un entier.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Quand on r&eacute;alise un h&eacute;ritage, la classe fille caract&eacute;rise un nouveau type mais est toujours du type de la m&egrave;re. Par exemple une pomme est toujours consid&eacute;r&eacute;e </span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">comme </span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">un fruit, qui est toujours consid&eacute;r&eacute; comme un v&eacute;g&eacute;tal. En programmation orient&eacute;e objet c&rsquo;est le m&ecirc;me concept, on parle alors de </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>hi&eacute;rarchie de types</strong></span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Comme tout bon langage objet, PHP dispose de l&rsquo;op&eacute;rateur </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>instanceOf</strong></span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> qui permet de savoir si une instance est d&rsquo;un type donn&eacute;. Cet op&eacute;rateur renvoie </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>true</strong></span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> si l&rsquo;objet est du type (ou </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">super-type</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">) sp&eacute;cifi&eacute;.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Exemple de hi&eacute;rarchie:</span></p>\r\n<table width=\"605\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\"><colgroup><col width=\"20\" /> <col width=\"577\" /> </colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 0cm;\" width=\"20\">\r\n<pre class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">1</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">2</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">3</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">4</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">5</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">6</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">7</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">8</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">9</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">10</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">11</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">12</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">13</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">14</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">15</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">16</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">17</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">18</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">19</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">20</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">21</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">22</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">23</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">24</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">25</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">26</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">27</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">28</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">29</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">30</span></pre>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 0cm;\" width=\"577\">\r\n<pre class=\"western\"><span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\"><span style=\"color: #006699;\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>&lt;?</strong></span></span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">php</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\"><span style=\"color: #ff5600;\">class</span> <span style=\"color: #21439c;\">Vivant</span></span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\">{</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\">}</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\"><span style=\"color: #ff5600;\">class</span> <span style=\"color: #21439c;\">Vegetal</span> <span style=\"color: #ff5600;\">extends</span> Vivant</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\">{</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\">}</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\"><span style=\"color: #ff5600;\">class</span> <span style=\"color: #21439c;\">Fruit</span> <span style=\"color: #ff5600;\">extends</span> Vegetal</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\">{</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\">}</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\"><span style=\"color: #ff5600;\">class</span> <span style=\"color: #21439c;\">Apple</span> <span style=\"color: #ff5600;\">extends</span> Fruit</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\">{</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\">}</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\"><span style=\"color: #ff5600;\">class</span> <span style=\"color: #21439c;\">GoldenLady</span> <span style=\"color: #ff5600;\">extends</span> Apple</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\">{</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\">}</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\">$object <span style=\"color: #006699;\"><strong>=</strong></span> <span style=\"color: #006699;\"><strong>new</strong></span> GoldenLady;</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\">var_dump( $object instanceOf <span style=\"color: #ff5600;\">Apple</span> );  <span style=\"color: #af82d4;\">// true</span></span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\">var_dump( $object instanceOf <span style=\"color: #ff5600;\">Fruit</span> );  <span style=\"color: #af82d4;\">// true</span></span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #3b3b3b;\">var_dump( $object instanceOf <span style=\"color: #ff5600;\">Vegetal</span>); <span style=\"color: #af82d4;\">// true</span></span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #af82d4;\">// ... etc.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #21439c;\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>?&gt;</strong></span></span>\r\n</pre>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p style=\"page-break-before: always;\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Il est d&rsquo;ailleurs possible de sp&eacute;cifier sur un prototype quel type d&rsquo;objet est attendu pour un param&egrave;tre donn&eacute;:</span></p>\r\n<table width=\"378\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\"><colgroup><col width=\"20\" /> <col width=\"350\" /> </colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 0cm;\" width=\"20\">\r\n<pre class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">1</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">2</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">3</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">4</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">5</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">6</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">7</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">8</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">9</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">10</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">11</span></pre>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 0cm;\" width=\"350\">\r\n<pre class=\"western\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.5cm;\">&nbsp;</pre>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">On appelle cette syntaxe de param&egrave;tres le </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>type-hinting</strong></span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">; c&rsquo;est &agrave; dire qu&rsquo;on demande explicitement des objets du type (ou super-type) sp&eacute;cifi&eacute;. N&rsquo;importe quoi d&rsquo;autre provoquera une erreur. Si on avait pass&eacute; un type natif comme un entier ou encore une instance qui h&eacute;rite de la classe </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Vegetal</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> mais qui n&rsquo;est pas un fruit, on se serait fait jeter.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Le type-hinting est extr&ecirc;mement pratique pour s&eacute;curiser vos fonctions et vos m&eacute;thodes en emp&ecirc;chant le d&eacute;veloppeur d&rsquo;y mettre n&rsquo;importe quoi.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Note</span></strong><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">: contrairement &agrave; d&rsquo;autres langages objets comme Java, les objets n&rsquo;h&eacute;ritent pas par d&eacute;faut de la class </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Object</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">, vous devez donc </span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">recourir</span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> &agrave; </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">is_object</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> si vous voulez valider le type objet.</span></p>\r\n<h2 class=\"western\"><a name=\"le-polymorphisme\"></a><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Le polymorphisme</span></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Le polymorphisme (du grec </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">plusieurs formes</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">) est le m&eacute;canisme gr&acirc;ce auquel une m&ecirc;me m&eacute;thode peut &ecirc;tre impl&eacute;ment&eacute;e par plusieurs types (donc plusieurs classes) favorisant ainsi la </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">g&eacute;n&eacute;ricit&eacute;</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">. </span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Concr&egrave;tement</span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">, si une m&eacute;thode est d&eacute;clar&eacute;e et/ou d&eacute;finie dans la classe parente d&rsquo;une classe donn&eacute;e, vous n&rsquo;avez pas &agrave; vous </span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">pr&eacute;occuper</span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> du type pr&eacute;cis de la fille avec laquelle vous travaillez pour l&rsquo;utiliser.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Par exemple, une m&eacute;thode </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>obtenirAire</strong></span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> est commune aux classes </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Cercle</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">, </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Carre</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> et </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Rectangle</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> qui h&eacute;ritent toutes de </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Forme</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">. Quand vous travaillez avec une instance de </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Forme</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">, vous n&rsquo;avez donc plus &agrave; vous soucier de savoir si c&rsquo;est un cercle, un carr&eacute; ou un rectangle pour obtenir son aire.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Comme dans la plupart des langages objet, le polymorphisme en PHP est un polymorphisme par </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">sous-typage</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> (ou </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">d&eacute;rivation</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">) c&rsquo;est &agrave; dire qu&rsquo;on va se servir de la red&eacute;finition de comportements pr&eacute;vue par l&rsquo;h&eacute;ritage pour faire du polymorphisme. Nous avons vu plus haut avec </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Vehicule</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">, </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Voiture</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> et </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Moto</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> qu&rsquo;il est possible de red&eacute;finir une m&eacute;thode de la classe m&egrave;re dans sa fille (en </span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">l&rsquo;occurrence</span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">, il s&rsquo;agissait de son constructeur). Nous allons maintenant voir qu&rsquo;il est possible d&rsquo;aller plus loin.</span></p>\r\n<h3 class=\"western\"><a name=\"abstraction\"></a><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Abstraction</span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">En </span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">programmation</span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> objet, il est possible de d&eacute;clarer des m&eacute;thodes dont la d&eacute;finition n&rsquo;est pas encore connue dans la classe m&egrave;re mais le seront dans une classe fille. On parle alors de </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>m&eacute;thodes abstraite</strong></span></em><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">s</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">. </span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>Une classe qui contient au moins une m&eacute;thode abstraite doit elle aussi &ecirc;tre d&eacute;clar&eacute;e abstraite</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> et ne peut plus &ecirc;tre instanci&eacute;e - vu que tout son code n&rsquo;est pas impl&eacute;ment&eacute;. On parle alors de </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">classe abstraite</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Une m&eacute;thode abstraite est pr&eacute;c&eacute;d&eacute;e du mot cl&eacute; </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">abstract</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> (idem pour la classe qui la porte) et ne peut pas avoir de corp</span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">s</span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Exemple de classe abstraite:</span></p>\r\n<table width=\"620\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\"><colgroup><col width=\"20\" /> <col width=\"592\" /> </colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 0cm;\" width=\"20\">\r\n<pre class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">1</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">2</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">3</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">4</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">5</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">6</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">7</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">8</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">9</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">10</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">11</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">12</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">13</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">14</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">15</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">16</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">17</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">18</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">19</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">20</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">21</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">22</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">23</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">24</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">25</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">26</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">27</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">28</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">29</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">30</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">31</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">32</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">33</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">34</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">35</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">36</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">37</span></pre>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 0cm;\" width=\"592\">\r\n<pre class=\"western\">&nbsp;</pre>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Par opposition, une classe qui d&eacute;finit l&rsquo;int&eacute;gralit&eacute; de ses comportements est souvent appel&eacute; <strong>classe </strong><strong>concr&egrave;te</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<h3 class=\"western\"><a name=\"interfaces\"></a><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Interfaces</span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Si toutes les m&eacute;thodes d&rsquo;une classe sont abstraites, cette classe est alors une </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">interface</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">. D&egrave;s lors, on utilise le mot cl&eacute; </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">interface</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> en lieu et place du mot cl&eacute; </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">class</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">. L&rsquo;int&eacute;r&ecirc;t principal des interfaces est que plusieurs d&rsquo;entre elles peuvent &ecirc;tre </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">r&eacute;alis&eacute;es</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> (ou </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">impl&eacute;ment&eacute;es</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">) par une m&ecirc;me classe. En somme </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">class\r\nA extend B implements C,D,E</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> est tout &agrave; fait valide.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">On croise d&rsquo;ailleurs </span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">fr&eacute;quemment</span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> des classes qui r&eacute;alisent plusieurs interfaces, c&rsquo;est le cas notamment de la classe PHP </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>ArrayIterator</strong></span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> qui r&eacute;alise </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>Iterator</strong></span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">, </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>Traversable</strong></span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">, </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>ArrayAccess</strong></span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">, </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>SeekableIterator</strong></span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">, </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>Countable</strong></span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> et </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>Serializable</strong></span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">En fait l&rsquo;interface donne une </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">&ldquo;forme&rdquo;</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> a notre classe : elle va d&eacute;finir comment celle-ci doit se </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">pr&eacute;senter</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> (</span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"><strong>par l&agrave; on entends quelles devront &ecirc;tre ses m&eacute;thodes</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">) mais pas comment elle doit se </span><em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">comporter</span></em><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">. Les it</span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">&eacute;r</span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">ateurs de la SPL en sont un bel exemple : tous les it&eacute;rateurs partagent des prototypes de m&eacute;thodes communs mais chacun les impl&eacute;mente</span><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">s</span> <span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">diff&eacute;remment.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Note</span></strong><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">: vu que toutes les m&eacute;thodes d&rsquo;une interface sont obligatoirement abstraites, il est inutile de le sp&eacute;cifier avec le mot cl&eacute; </span><code class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">abstract</span></code><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\"> sur les m&eacute;thodes et la classe.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">Exemple d&rsquo;interface:</span></p>\r\n<table width=\"631\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\"><colgroup><col width=\"20\" /> <col width=\"603\" /> </colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 0cm;\" width=\"20\">\r\n<pre class=\"western\"><span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">1</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">2</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">3</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">4</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">5</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">6</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">7</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">8</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">9</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">10</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Frutiger;\">11</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-famil